The paper proposes a method for temporal action localization in videos using deep learning techniques. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The method involves a classification module and a deep metric learning module, which are both machine learning techniques falling under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also discusses the optimization of the loss function, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed method on two datasets, which involves information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques for comparing the results with the ground truth.
